---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHeader from '../components/PageHeader.astro';
import InfoBox from '../components/InfoBox.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Basic Care | Monarch Chihuahuas"
  description="Essential care tips for your new Chihuahua puppy from Monarch Chihuahuas."
  keywords="chihuahua care, chihuahua care tips, chihuahua puppy care"
>
  <PageHeader
    title="Basic Care"
    subtitle="Everything you need to know about caring for your Chihuahua"
  />

  <section class="info-content">
    <div class="content-container">
      <h2>Caring for Your Chihuahua Puppy</h2>
      <p>Chihuahuas are devoted little companions that thrive with proper nutrition, gentle handling, and lots of love. Their tiny size means they need a few special considerations to stay healthy and happy. Here's everything you need to know.</p>

      <h3>Feeding</h3>
      <p>Proper nutrition is essential, and because Chihuahuas are so small, every meal matters.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Puppies (8-12 weeks):</strong> Feed 4 small meals daily with a high-quality puppy food formulated for toy breeds</li>
        <li><strong>Puppies (3-6 months):</strong> 3 meals daily</li>
        <li><strong>Adults (6+ months):</strong> 2 small meals daily is typically sufficient</li>
      </ul>

      <InfoBox type="warning" title="Important">
        <p>Chihuahua puppies can be prone to hypoglycemia (low blood sugar) because of their tiny size. Never let your puppy go more than 4 hours without food, and keep a little honey or nutri-gel on hand for emergencies. Always feed a toy-breed-specific food.</p>
      </InfoBox>

      <h3>Exercise</h3>
      <p>Chihuahuas have surprisingly big energy in a tiny package, but their exercise needs are modest:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>20-30 minutes of light exercise daily</li>
        <li>Short, gentle walks (their little legs tire quickly)</li>
        <li>Indoor play sessions with soft toys</li>
        <li>Mental stimulation through puzzle toys and basic training</li>
        <li>Avoid jumping from heights — their bones are delicate</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Socialization</h3>
      <p>Early, positive socialization is crucial for a confident adult Chihuahua:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Expose them to different people, sounds, and gentle handling from a young age</li>
        <li>Enroll in puppy socialization classes designed for small breeds</li>
        <li>Calm introductions to other dogs build confidence and prevent fearfulness</li>
        <li>Carry them outside in busy environments until vaccinations are complete</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Grooming</h3>
      <p>Grooming a Chihuahua is one of the easiest jobs in the dog world:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Smooth coats:</strong> Weekly brushing with a soft bristle brush</li>
        <li><strong>Long coats:</strong> 2-3x weekly brushing to prevent tangles</li>
        <li><strong>Bathing:</strong> Every 4-6 weeks or as needed — Chihuahuas have sensitive skin</li>
        <li><strong>Warmth:</strong> A sweater for cold weather (they chill easily)</li>
      </ul>

      <InfoBox type="tip" title="Regular Maintenance">
        <ul>
          <li>Trim nails every 2-3 weeks (they don't wear down naturally)</li>
          <li>Clean ears weekly and check for redness</li>
          <li>Brush teeth daily — small breeds are prone to dental issues</li>
          <li>Check eyes for tear staining and gently wipe with a damp cloth</li>
        </ul>
      </InfoBox>

      <h3>Training</h3>
      <p>Chihuahuas are clever and pick up training quickly when it's done with patience:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Start training early and be very consistent</li>
        <li>Use positive reinforcement — never scold harshly</li>
        <li>Keep training sessions short (5-10 minutes)</li>
        <li>Socialize widely to prevent over-protective tendencies</li>
        <li>Be firm but gentle — they respond to calm leadership</li>
        <li>Crate training and potty training take patience but pay off</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="cta-box">
        <h3>Need More Guidance?</h3>
        <p>We're always here to help with any questions about caring for your Chihuahua.</p>
        <a href="/contact" class="btn">Contact Us</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .info-content {
    padding: 4rem 1.5rem;
    background: #fff;
  }

  .content-container {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #2B2018;
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
  }

  h3 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    margin: 2rem 0 1rem;
  }

  p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: #5a5a5a;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }

  ul {
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem 1.5rem;
    color: #5a5a5a;
  }

  li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .cta-box {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-primary), var(--color-primary));
    color: white;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 12px;
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .cta-box h3 {
    color: white;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .cta-box p {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .btn {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--color-primary);
    color: white;
    padding: 0.875rem 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }

  .btn:hover {
    background: var(--color-secondary);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .info-content {
      padding: 3rem 1rem;
    }

    h2 {
      font-size: 1.75rem;
    }

    h3 {
      font-size: 1.25rem;
    }
  }
</style>
